\begin{abstract}
This document aims at presenting Social security contributions (SSC) in France with an historical perspective. Rules for SSC are described including the definition of tax base, changes in employer and employee SSC, the introduction of flat rate income taxes (CSG and CRDS) in replacement of SSC and the specific payroll taxes -- employer SSC which fall on specific firms.
\end{abstract}
