\subsection{Special tax on employer's contributions to contingency funds}

The contributions paid by employers or representative institutions for wage-earning workers to contingency funds, in order to provide them additional benefits, are subjected to a tax entirely supported by employers and equivalent to 8\% of these contributions. However, pension contributions do not enter the tax base, and companies with less than nine employees are exempt since 1997. A 2010 law has also integrated into the tax base the contributions paid for former employees.


