The widening of the exemption plan was part of a movement of inclusion in the budget of the family benefits financing. Concerns have been raised about a possible freeze of the earnings triggered by the first exemption law of 1993: indeed, if the employers pay less or no contributions on low wages, they have less interest to increase the wage above the exemption level. A response to that is to progressively raise the exemption ceiling, which has been made in 1994.\\
The exemption has also been extended to employers whose employees are affiliated to special schemes of the social security.

